http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Warmer-days-in-the-offing/article14020466.ece

Winter set in rather late in the city this year and brought with it foggy days, icy-cold mornings and chilly winds. However, just as cold-day conditions started to get Delhiites feeling uncomfortable, the forecast shows that there will be a steady rise in temperatures over the week.From a cold maximum of 16. 3 degrees Celsius on Sunday, the maximum temperature settled at 18.7 degrees Celsius on Monday. The maximum is expected to rise further and settle at 20 degrees Celsius on Tuesday, which will be the normal temperature for this time of the year. It will rise steadily by one-two degrees later in the week, according to the Meteorological Department.